1
00:00:01,069 --> 00:00:05,360
One of the most difficult market conditions
is the notorious sideways market, which can

2
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:08,210
affect trading performance if you fail to
adjust accordingly.

3
00:00:08,210 --> 00:00:13,150
In this video, I will share a step by step
process to help you tackle a sideways market

4
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:16,910
for potentially better trading results.

5
00:00:16,910 --> 00:00:20,369
Step number one is to learn to identify a
sideways market.

6
00:00:20,369 --> 00:00:24,610
This step seems intuitive and obvious but
is often ignored by traders.

7
00:00:24,610 --> 00:00:29,980
A sideways market is obviously one where price
action will not roll in one definitive direction,

8
00:00:29,980 --> 00:00:35,690
(up or down) but run side to side through
short bursts of movements up AND down, reflecting

9
00:00:35,690 --> 00:00:38,550
major indecision in the market.

10
00:00:38,550 --> 00:00:43,420
A consolidation or sideways phase in the market
may be easy to spot – even for newer traders

11
00:00:43,420 --> 00:00:48,120
– when it has already formed, but can be
a real challenge to spot as it is forming

12
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:52,310
when the market is transitioning from a trending
phase to a consolidation phase.

13
00:00:52,310 --> 00:00:57,489
It will usually take traders quite a few losses
before they eventually realize the market

14
00:00:57,489 --> 00:01:01,949
has lost the trend and decisive direction.

15
00:01:01,949 --> 00:01:06,570
Contrary to a trending market, a sideways
market will often comprise of brief periods

16
00:01:06,570 --> 00:01:11,730
of strong price action in one direction that
will often reverse shortly after, usually

17
00:01:11,730 --> 00:01:15,680
from short term support and resistance levels
formed recently.

18
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:21,140
As illustrated in this example, many short
term levels in a narrow range form a key characteristic

19
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:25,829
of consolidation phases themselves and can
be early indicators of a market that could

20
00:01:25,829 --> 00:01:29,369
possibly be transitioning into a sideways
phase.

21
00:01:29,369 --> 00:01:34,049
On the contrary, a strong trending market
will usually pack enough strength to push

22
00:01:34,049 --> 00:01:37,939
through minor areas with relative ease.

23
00:01:37,939 --> 00:01:40,270
Step number 2: define the range

24
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:44,780
Once you have identified that your market
is in (or is entering) a consolidation phase,

25
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:50,500
one of the first steps to take is to clearly
establish the limits or the range of the consolidation

26
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:51,630
phase itself.

27
00:01:51,630 --> 00:01:56,969
Usually, these phases will have a clearly
defined upper and lower range, marked by either

28
00:01:56,969 --> 00:02:03,200
side to side support and resistance levels
or angular trend lines and channels.

29
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:07,229
Identifying the range is practically marking
out your battle field, meaning how much of

30
00:02:07,229 --> 00:02:09,810
a playing field do you actually possess.

31
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:15,130
And this is very important because a consolidation
phase that is too narrow, it’s not worth

32
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:16,280
trading at all.

33
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:21,830
You need ranges wide enough to allow you to
trade with caution.

34
00:02:21,830 --> 00:02:27,130
The wider the range the more ‘space’ you
technically have to take and manage your trade.

35
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:32,540
In a very narrow range, as the one in this
chart, trading could be more risky as trouble

36
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:37,900
areas and potential support and resistance
levels could be grouped very close together,

37
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:43,040
making it hard to expect much from price movements.

38
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:47,410
Defining the range gives you a more clear
perspective of the bigger picture.

39
00:02:47,410 --> 00:02:51,650
Knowing the upper and lower limits of the
trading range also allows you to watch the

40
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:55,310
range itself for a potential breakout to either
side.

41
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:59,910
This is especially useful when the top and
bottom levels of the consolidation phase are

42
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:04,920
defined by angular trend lines, like in a
wedge pattern that is slowly constricting

43
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:08,110
price action, leading to a possible breakout.

44
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:14,840
Step no.3: Identify the mid range and other
internal levels of support/resistance

45
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:19,130
The next step is to highlight all the areas
within the trading range that could potentially

46
00:03:19,130 --> 00:03:21,770
cause price to hold as support or resistance.

47
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:24,870
They key here is to identify all levels.

48
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:30,330
Often, traders will be glued to the larger
more obvious regions, which in the case of

49
00:03:30,330 --> 00:03:37,350
consolidating markets is often just the top
and lower end of the consolidation range itself.

50
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:41,730
The trick is to identify ALL levels of potential
support and resistance.

51
00:03:41,730 --> 00:03:47,070
In a weak market that is struggling for sustained
momentum, even the minor areas of support

52
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:50,150
and resistance can cause the price to hold
up.

53
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:54,751
Hence all possible troubles areas – major
and minor – need to be settled into your

54
00:03:54,751 --> 00:03:57,330
trade management and planning phase.

55
00:03:57,330 --> 00:04:02,240
While doing so doesn’t entirely eliminate
the notorious ‘surprise’ factor of a sideways

56
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:08,950
market, it does eliminate a lot of ambiguity
around the seemingly unpredictable price action.

57
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:13,760
Of prime importance in sideways markets is
often the mid range of the area.

58
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:18,820
The mid range tends to act as a pivot for
the price as it moves back and forth from

59
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,850
the consolidation range.

60
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:25,930
This is basically the 50% Fibonacci level
between the range high and the range low.

61
00:04:25,930 --> 00:04:32,161
Generally, above the mid range price is bullish
and below the mid range is bearish, range

62
00:04:32,161 --> 00:04:37,700
high will act as resistance and the range
low will act as support.

63
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:42,340
Now, even though you may have outlined all
the possible areas on the chart that could

64
00:04:42,340 --> 00:04:47,380
potentially cause trouble for the price as
it hits these regions, you need to factor

65
00:04:47,380 --> 00:04:52,750
in the uncertainty that comes along with trading
in a weak non-decisive market.

66
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:57,560
Just as the price can bounce and spike up
and down the short and long-term levels within

67
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:03,180
the consolidation range, it may still be prone
to spikes or otherwise strong and sudden periods

68
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:08,820
of sharp movements in either direction off
a seemingly clear level within the range.

69
00:05:08,820 --> 00:05:12,440
This likelihood calls for a safe and conservative
trading style.

70
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:17,560
Whether that involves placing conservative
stops on the chart, using trailing stops,

71
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:22,160
watching the trade live (if you day trade
or scalp the market) or taking quick profits

72
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:28,150
at brief intervals, you must take all actions
necessary to safeguard yourself from reversing

73
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:30,630
market action.

74
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:35,400
Take a look at this example of a seemingly
unpredictable bounce during sideways market

75
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,400
action.

76
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:40,730
Notice how price pulls back from the region
marked with this circle, even though it would

77
00:05:40,730 --> 00:05:45,400
be hard to categorize the area as a clear
support and resistance level.

78
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:50,090
We are well under the top end of the range
and also further away from the midrange support

79
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:51,110
and resistance level.

80
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:56,300
It is these kinds of pullbacks that require
conservative trade management when the market

81
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:59,500
is choppy and indecisive.

82
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:02,150
You need to find a Balance between Aggression
and Conservation.

83
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:06,830
While it’s very important not to be over
aggressive when trading a sideways market,

84
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:11,620
it is also just as important not to be ultra
conservative either.

85
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:16,639
In a sideways market, because market sentiment
is weak, managing the trade too tight can

86
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:22,180
often result in a ‘suffocated’ trade as
price whipsaws within the trading range bouncing

87
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:27,300
off minor and major support and resistance
levels found internally within the range.

88
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:32,980
For example, moving the stop to breakeven
as soon as a trade moves in a sideways market

89
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:35,310
holds a very strong chance of hitting it.

90
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:40,230
The strategy could well have been intended
to safeguard against choppy price action,

91
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:45,080
but ultra-conservative trade management doesn’t
help record consistent results in a sideways

92
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,380
market either.

93
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:52,240
It is easy to see how several trades executed
in a sideways market – each resulting in

94
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:57,980
either a breakeven trade or a minor loss–
because of adopting ultra conservative trade

95
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:01,350
management-, would not be benefiting your
account equity much at all.

96
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:06,510
In fact, for such a trader, avoiding trading
in a sideways market altogether might actually

97
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:10,690
be a smarter move as that eliminates the risk
entirely.

98
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:14,940
But for other traders who wish to improve
their sideways market trading skills, it is

99
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:19,139
crucial to find the perfect balance between
aggression and conservation when it comes

100
00:07:19,139 --> 00:07:21,820
to trade management.

101
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:26,540
Sometimes a chart can look messy and it can
be difficult to choose a range high and range

102
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:27,540
low.

103
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:31,050
It can be just as simple as picking the range
that fits the best.

104
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:36,680
Try different possibilities and see where
and how price reacts to a certain level.

105
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,660
Also, look for confluence.

106
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:43,740
If multiple important levels line up, it’s
more likely price will reject or bounce at

107
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:44,870
that level.

108
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:50,050
This confluence can include an important support,
resistance, or even a moving average if you

109
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:52,280
use one.

110
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:56,620
There are many ways to trade a range, but
let me share the strategies that work for

111
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:57,620
me.

112
00:07:57,620 --> 00:08:02,080
The classic trade is to search for price action
patterns at the upper and lower levels of

113
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:05,800
the range, trading the bounce from that levels.

114
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:09,680
My favorite range trading strategy is fading
the breakout.

115
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:15,540
You need to search for this scenario: a low
broken after a down move or a high broken

116
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:17,130
after up move.

117
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:22,390
Next, I wait for a close back inside the range
or even for a retest.

118
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:27,810
Stop loss below/above the failed breakout,
meaning the most recent lows (or highs) and

119
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:31,880
I target range high (or low), depending on
the case.

120
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:37,979
Also, if the range is wide enough, trading
the midrange can provide high probability

121
00:08:37,979 --> 00:08:38,979
setups.

122
00:08:38,979 --> 00:08:43,890
Above the mid-range price is bullish, below
the mid range, price is bearish.

123
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:46,310
And here is an important tip.

124
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:51,440
Even though we are in a range, the previous
trend of an asset is obviously very important.

125
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:57,040
A trade that goes with the recent trend is
more likely to play out compared to a trade

126
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,360
against the trend.

127
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:03,280
I prefer to trade range setups that go with
the previous trend, so they have a higher

128
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:06,380
probability of playing out.

129
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:11,240
Trading a range can just utilize support and
resistance levels, but it can also involve

130
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,170
the use of indicators.

131
00:09:13,170 --> 00:09:17,740
Such technical indicators, such as the Relative
Strength Index (RSI) or Stochastics can be

132
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:23,420
utilized to confirm the overbought and oversold
conditions that often follow price movements

133
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:26,420
at the top and bottom of a trading range.

134
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:32,360
Or can reveal a divergence at the top or bottom
of the range, which can be a powerful sign

135
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:37,700
that the range will hold and a trade inside
the range can be taken.

136
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:42,650
Range trading is a very useful skill to have
because most markets don’t trend all of

137
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,650
the time.

138
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:48,420
If you correctly identify the range, time
your entry and control your risk exposure

139
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:54,330
you can make some decent profits even if the
markets are not moving decisive in one direction.

140
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:58,400
As always, if you learned something new and
found value, leave us a like to show your

141
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:02,650
support, subscribe to our channel and click
the bell icon to stay in touch when we release

142
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:03,760
new videos.

143
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,680
Until next time.

